RACE.FOOTNOTES: BENEDICT CANYON broke out, unhurried early on and moved inward, closed in around the turn on the inside under patient handling, exited the bend two wide, rallied between in upper stretch and drove clear. PROCRASTINATION stalked the top pair up the backstretch, loomed three wide into the stretch, launched a bid four deep in upper stretch but got outkicked by BENEDICTA CANYON in the late stages. DENIM IN GOLD stumbled badly leaving the gate, jumped onto the dirt crossing, raced outside a rival into the turn, spun three wide into the lane and was along for the show. POWER SURGE broke a step slow then was sent to press the pace from inside, dueled around the turn along the rail, fought to the eighth pole and weakened. LIV AND LET LIV set the pace outside POWER SURGE up the backstretch, dueled with that rival around the bend, fought to upper stretch then weakened in the final furlong.
